Minister of Youth and Sports, Barrister Solomon Dalung has congratulated former Super Eagles Technical Adviser, Chief Adegboye Onigbinde on the occasion of his 80th birthday on Monday, March 5. The Minister, who joined millions of football lovers and well meaning Nigerians to wish the octogenarian a happy birthday thanked God for keeping him for eight decades. Dalung described Onigbinde who led the Super Eagles to the 2002 World Cup in Korea/Japan as an achiever and a hero who had paid his dues in the development of Nigerian football. “Chief Adegboye Onigbinde is a highly respected Nigerian soccer tactician who also served as CAF and FIFA Technical instructor. “His contributions to the development of football in the country are greatly appreciated. On this special day, we pray that God will preserve his life with good health. We wish him many more years.” Dalung said. Chief Onigbinde was in charge of Shooting Stars Sports Club (3SC) of Ibadan in 1984 when the club reached the final of the Africa Club Champions Cup. Same year, he led Nigeria to the final of the Africa Cup of Nations. Onigbinde was a former FIFA Technical Adviser, CAF Technical Committee member and two–time Head Coach of the Super Eagles of Nigeria. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.